1
00:00:40,006 --> 00:00:41,775
You didn't have to.

2
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:01,528
Armand de Brignac Blanc de Blancs.

3
00:01:02,195 --> 00:01:05,331
It's the wine you always ordered for me
but never got to drink yourself.

4
00:01:06,299 --> 00:01:07,734
Today, I ordered it for you.

5
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:33,993
I'd like to introduce myself again.

6
00:01:36,596 --> 00:01:38,665
My name is Jeong Gal-hee.

7
00:01:39,232 --> 00:01:41,501
Dad passed away when I was 12,

8
00:01:41,734 --> 00:01:43,870
and Mom passed away when I was 19.

9
00:01:44,804 --> 00:01:48,274
I have no money or parents.
I have nothing.

10
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:51,778
But I have a big brother and
a little sister, who always root for me.

11
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:56,015
At work, I have amazing secretary friends.

12
00:01:57,150 --> 00:02:00,653
And I work for a great boss

13
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,023
who overlooks my mistakes.

14
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:07,193
I see.

15
00:02:08,761 --> 00:02:10,029
So that's who you are.

16
00:02:11,197 --> 00:02:12,365
As you already know,

17
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:14,601
I'm Do Min-ik.

18
00:02:15,935 --> 00:02:19,672
The crazy guy who fell in love
with both sides of you.

19
00:02:25,178 --> 00:02:26,312
Shall we make a toast?

20
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:28,848
To what?

21
00:02:29,716 --> 00:02:32,318
To our first encounter

22
00:02:33,286 --> 00:02:35,021
as Jeong Gal-hee and Do Min-ik.

23
00:02:49,202 --> 00:02:50,603
I don't think they're from this floor.

24
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:52,605
-What happened?
-What's this?

25
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,040
A "breach of confidence"?

26
00:02:54,741 --> 00:02:56,142
"T&T Mobile hereby announces

27
00:02:56,209 --> 00:02:58,444
a disciplinary meeting
for all permanent employees

28
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:01,481
and dispatched workers
involved in the improper group, Euldoguk,

29
00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:03,917
as well as the termination
of the dispatched workers' contracts."

30
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:07,253
No way.

31
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:09,489
"Mr. Gi and Ms. Lee will be punished
on the following grounds.

32
00:03:09,756 --> 00:03:11,491
By establishing
the improper group, Euldoguk,

33
00:03:11,558 --> 00:03:14,093
-Ms. Lee disturbed the order..."
-Hi, Ri-ra.

34
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:17,263
-"...while Mr. Gi cooperated with Ms. Lee.
-What?

35
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:20,233
-Also, dispatched workers in Euldoguk..."
-Darn it.

36
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,935
"Damaged the company's

37
00:03:22,001 --> 00:03:24,304
reputation and credibility
by leaking company secrets.

38
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:26,372
The dispatched workers' contracts
are hereby terminated."

39
00:03:26,739 --> 00:03:27,974
-Myeong-jeong.
-Hey.

40
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:30,176
What do we do now?

41
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:50,897
Guys, what are we supposed to do now?

42
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:53,766
If you don't cancel their dismissal,
I'll accuse you

43
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:56,236
of exchange of favors,
breach of trust, and bribery.

44
00:03:56,803 --> 00:03:59,339
If a breach of trust was so easy to prove,

45
00:03:59,606 --> 00:04:01,040
I wouldn't be in my position by now.

46
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:03,910
Regarding bribes, luckily,
you guys pocketed enough money

47
00:04:03,977 --> 00:04:05,712
so that it'd be no problem.

48
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:09,382
If the law can't punish you,
we'll go to the press...

49
00:04:11,384 --> 00:04:13,086
There are a ton of people

50
00:04:13,152 --> 00:04:14,721
who have pocketed more money than I have.

51
00:04:15,154 --> 00:04:18,191
Go ahead and try. Fine, I accepted
a few paintings and offered some money.

52
00:04:18,257 --> 00:04:19,859
Who'd write about that?

53
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:24,063
It's got a stain.

54
00:04:24,130 --> 00:04:25,164
CEO SIM HAE-YONG

55
00:04:28,301 --> 00:04:31,037
Neither you nor I want the ledger
to be exposed.

56
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,839
Why don't we wrap it up here?

57
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:38,244
Be grateful that I'm not suing you
for embezzlement.

58
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:58,998
I'm sorry that you've been
feeling so anxious.

59
00:05:13,012 --> 00:05:16,015
Gal-hee, can't you take the day off?

60
00:05:24,257 --> 00:05:27,193
The weather is so nice. Let's go
on a picnic with Nam-hee or something.

61
00:05:31,097 --> 00:05:33,099
On a beautiful, sunny day like this,

62
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:35,201
going on a picnic isn't what I want.

63
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:39,105
I want to go to work.

64
00:05:40,073 --> 00:05:44,277
Baby, come to work with me.

65
00:05:47,947 --> 00:05:49,115
Who is it?

66
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:57,290
Mr. Do, what are you doing here?

67
00:05:58,758 --> 00:05:59,959
Who is he?

68
00:06:00,393 --> 00:06:02,462
That's my little sister, Nam-hee.

69
00:06:02,829 --> 00:06:05,164
Hello, I'm Do Min-ik.

70
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:07,967
Let me go and get my bag.

71
00:06:09,001 --> 00:06:11,204
Do I look like I'm going to work?

72
00:06:13,072 --> 00:06:14,240
Are you visiting somewhere?

73
00:06:15,441 --> 00:06:18,411
We're going on a date. A date.

74
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:21,681
What's going on?
Are you going out with your boss?

75
00:06:21,748 --> 00:06:22,815
A date?

76
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:26,652
What about work?

77
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:29,322
Take the day off.
You can tell your boss right now.

78
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:31,691
How...

79
00:06:32,925 --> 00:06:35,128
Can I take the day off?

80
00:06:35,328 --> 00:06:36,429
Yes, you can.

81
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:41,501
Why couldn't you tell me earlier?

82
00:06:42,201 --> 00:06:46,205
My hair is a mess, and
I'm not even wearing any makeup.

83
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:48,941
Remember? Your boss

84
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:50,676
can't see people's faces.

85
00:06:51,944 --> 00:06:53,112
Still,

86
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:55,782
this is our first date.

87
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,584
I would've loved to put on pretty clothes

88
00:06:59,685 --> 00:07:01,187
for you.

89
00:07:03,322 --> 00:07:05,291
I'll be waiting in the car.

90
00:07:05,892 --> 00:07:07,193
Take your time.

91
00:07:07,794 --> 00:07:08,628
Okay.

92
00:07:10,963 --> 00:07:12,632
-Bye.
-Bye.

93
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,034
Mr. Do.

94
00:07:50,203 --> 00:07:51,304
Well...

95
00:07:52,505 --> 00:07:53,639
You look pretty.

96
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,341
You think so?

97
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:58,010
I just took off my glasses.

98
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:00,880
Why did you bring that cardigan though?

99
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:03,249
You could've worn anything you wanted.

100
00:08:03,883 --> 00:08:08,187
You wanted to be able to recognize
at least one person in the world.

101
00:08:09,021 --> 00:08:12,425
I feel the same. I want you
to be able to recognize me

102
00:08:12,859 --> 00:08:15,595
no matter what.

103
00:08:19,732 --> 00:08:22,034
Do you remember the concert
at the Center for Performing Arts

104
00:08:22,535 --> 00:08:24,537
we were going to watch?

105
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:27,673
Why don't we see it today?

106
00:08:27,807 --> 00:08:29,475
Sure. I'll book the tickets right away.

107
00:08:31,777 --> 00:08:32,945
I already did.

108
00:08:34,313 --> 00:08:36,816
I just wanted to know
if you'd like to see it.

109
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:38,584
Well...

110
00:08:39,118 --> 00:08:42,388
Anything would be fun
as long as I doing it with you.

111
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:52,532
Please, Mr. Do.

112
00:09:02,341 --> 00:09:04,777
Please, Ms. Jeong.

113
00:09:09,348 --> 00:09:11,150
The car looks amazing.

114
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:16,322
By the way, where are you two headed?

115
00:09:18,658 --> 00:09:21,060
Well, we're just...

116
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:23,896
Nam-hee, let them enjoy their date.

117
00:09:24,664 --> 00:09:25,898
I apologize, Mr. Do.

118
00:09:25,965 --> 00:09:28,234
Please don't mind us.

119
00:09:28,501 --> 00:09:30,670
I hope you two have a great time.

120
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:41,881
Goodness. While perfectly healthy people
ride a nice car,

121
00:09:42,181 --> 00:09:44,584
a blind man has to walk.

122
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:50,790
Oh, my. Isn't that sad?

123
00:09:55,995 --> 00:09:57,496
I'm sorry, Mr. Do.

124
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:59,899
Don't be.

125
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:03,402
They don't have a car.
We should, of course, give them a ride.

126
00:10:03,903 --> 00:10:05,838
Where can I drop you off?

127
00:10:06,672 --> 00:10:09,742
Can you drop us off at the nearest beach?

128
00:10:10,710 --> 00:10:11,744
A beach?

129
00:10:11,811 --> 00:10:14,046
We booked tickets for a concert.

130
00:10:14,513 --> 00:10:15,815
Nam-hee, you know this, right?

131
00:10:16,382 --> 00:10:19,018
The only luxury
a blind man like me can afford is

132
00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:22,088
some fresh air.

133
00:10:22,888 --> 00:10:24,857
That girl is blinded with love right now.

134
00:10:24,924 --> 00:10:28,127
She wouldn't give a darn
about her blind brother.

135
00:10:28,494 --> 00:10:31,030
Nam-hee, will you stop?

136
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:33,666
I can take you to the beach.

137
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,768
We don't have time to do that.

138
00:10:37,203 --> 00:10:40,573
I've been looking forward
to our first date so much.

139
00:10:41,107 --> 00:10:43,909
I really wanted us
to be by ourselves today.

140
00:10:45,411 --> 00:10:46,846
First,

141
00:10:47,413 --> 00:10:49,849
we'll drop them off at the beach.

142
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:52,585
And then we can be by ourselves.

143
00:10:53,386 --> 00:10:55,955
We'll have grilled clams
like the last time

144
00:10:56,288 --> 00:10:57,757
and go to a nice cafe.

145
00:11:02,228 --> 00:11:03,362
That sounds good.

146
00:11:24,717 --> 00:11:26,052
This feels so light.

147
00:11:31,223 --> 00:11:32,758
Catch me if you can!

148
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:35,327
Jung-hee!

149
00:11:35,728 --> 00:11:38,230
-Wait, Jung-hee!
-He said we'd be by ourselves.

150
00:11:45,905 --> 00:11:47,873
-Jung-hee!
-Try and catch me!

151
00:11:51,610 --> 00:11:53,646
I thought you said we'd be by ourselves.

152
00:11:53,813 --> 00:11:57,116
I'm just worried
he'll fall into the water.

153
00:11:57,616 --> 00:12:00,019
Let me hang out with him
just a little longer.

154
00:12:00,319 --> 00:12:03,055
We can have dinner
by ourselves later, I promise.

155
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:05,257
This is it.

156
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:07,226
We can leave Jung-hee to Nam-hee.

157
00:12:07,293 --> 00:12:08,861
-We should go now.
-Right now?

158
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,296
-Let's go!
-Wait.

159
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:53,372
You didn't have to wear high heels.

160
00:13:00,312 --> 00:13:01,447
There you go.

161
00:13:05,084 --> 00:13:07,052
May I ask you something?

162
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:08,621
I think I'm lost.

163
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:11,690
Can you help me find
my sister and her boyfriend?

164
00:13:11,757 --> 00:13:16,095
They were around here a minute ago.

165
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:18,030
I lost them while playing tag.

166
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:42,988
Didn't you say
we'd have dinner by ourselves?

167
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:44,356
I mean...

168
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,893
He got hungry after running around.
What can we do about that?

169
00:13:49,094 --> 00:13:51,831
Let him have some food first.

170
00:13:56,769 --> 00:13:58,370
Jung-hee.

171
00:13:58,804 --> 00:14:01,373
Are you sure you can't see?

172
00:14:01,774 --> 00:14:05,010
How can you know exactly
where the meat is every time?

173
00:14:05,077 --> 00:14:06,312
I'm not sure.

174
00:14:06,779 --> 00:14:09,982
At this moment, it's as if I can see.

175
00:14:15,387 --> 00:14:17,590
Are you done? Let's go.

176
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:19,592
Mr. Do.

177
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:23,329
Oh, okay.

178
00:14:23,896 --> 00:14:26,432
Nam-hee. This is the first time

179
00:14:26,498 --> 00:14:29,168
I've eaten Korean beef
since the 2010 World Cup.

180
00:14:29,268 --> 00:14:30,302
What about you?

181
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:33,339
For me, this is the first time ever.

182
00:14:34,106 --> 00:14:36,442
Until now, I only ate
US and Australian beef.

183
00:14:36,575 --> 00:14:38,744
I didn't even know
Korea produced beef too.

184
00:14:38,978 --> 00:14:41,113
I thought all meat was frozen.

185
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,048
I didn't know
you could buy fresh meat too.

186
00:14:43,649 --> 00:14:46,151
Mr. Do, you know what?

187
00:14:46,785 --> 00:14:49,288
My family wasn't affected
by the IMF crisis at all.

188
00:14:50,656 --> 00:14:52,124
We were always poor.

189
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:58,898
Excuse me! Three more portions, please.

190
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,033
Coming up.

191
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:03,102
Mr. Do.

192
00:15:07,673 --> 00:15:08,807
Well...

193
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:11,410
No. The moment you drink that,

194
00:15:11,477 --> 00:15:15,414
we're trapped here forever.

195
00:15:17,816 --> 00:15:18,851
Of course.

196
00:15:18,918 --> 00:15:22,154
You probably get to enjoy
expensive liquors all the time.

197
00:15:22,221 --> 00:15:24,490
You wouldn't care for soju
poured by a blind man.

198
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:28,627
I'll drink it.

199
00:15:45,377 --> 00:15:47,179
BED AND BREAKFAST, WE HAVE VACANCIES

200
00:15:53,552 --> 00:15:57,589
Do you expect me to let you stay here?

201
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:01,360
So why did you drink that soju?

202
00:16:01,427 --> 00:16:03,128
You drank too.

203
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:09,535
I don't think this is a good idea.

204
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:12,638
Why don't we wait until I sober up

205
00:16:12,705 --> 00:16:14,039
and go back to Seoul?

206
00:16:14,106 --> 00:16:16,675
Why didn't you make a reservation
beforehand?

207
00:16:16,742 --> 00:16:18,877
It's impossible to get rooms
this late around here.

208
00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:21,780
Since he's a director and everything,

209
00:16:21,914 --> 00:16:23,682
I thought he'd take us
to a six-star hotel.

210
00:16:24,383 --> 00:16:27,219
You're the ones who changed
the destination all of a sudden.

211
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:31,123
I can't even tell whether
this is a six-star hotel or an inn.

212
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:33,993
Being blind sure comes in handy sometimes.

213
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:39,832
Maybe this is a good thing.

214
00:16:40,432 --> 00:16:41,567
What?

215
00:16:41,734 --> 00:16:44,370
Let's make those two go to sleep soon.

216
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:48,140
Then we can spend a long, long night

217
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:52,478
just the two of us.

218
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:04,757
If you're ready, shoot!

219
00:17:09,294 --> 00:17:10,763
GWANGBAK BUILDING

220
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:14,266
You win Gwangbak Building
near Gangnam Station!

221
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,168
What are you doing?

222
00:17:16,502 --> 00:17:18,237
The thing is,

223
00:17:18,737 --> 00:17:21,907
in return for being such a dirty guy
for me last night,

224
00:17:22,574 --> 00:17:26,678
I'd love to give you a little something.

225
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:29,415
But what could I possibly give you?

226
00:17:29,481 --> 00:17:31,517
I have nothing but money and buildings.

227
00:17:31,917 --> 00:17:35,687
So I decided to give you
one of my buildings as a present.

228
00:17:37,656 --> 00:17:40,659
What I want is not the building,
but the owner of it.

229
00:17:41,326 --> 00:17:45,064
Also, last night, I wasn't being
a dirty guy for you,

230
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,899
but for myself.

231
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:51,303
Wait, please don't be like that.

232
00:17:51,370 --> 00:17:54,873
You're making me
want to give you even more.

233
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,543
What should I give you? What do you want?

234
00:17:57,976 --> 00:18:00,279
You don't have a car, do you?
Should I get one for you?

235
00:18:00,345 --> 00:18:02,848
Pick one. A sedan,
a sports car, or an SUV?

236
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:04,983
The very reason why I can be so dirty

237
00:18:05,050 --> 00:18:08,220
happens to be my strong thighs,
trained by years of bike riding.

238
00:18:08,821 --> 00:18:11,623
Are you sure about this?
Can you really give up on these thighs?

239
00:18:12,324 --> 00:18:13,392
I can't.

240
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:16,495
Why do I become so stupid

241
00:18:16,662 --> 00:18:18,997
when I'm with you?

242
00:18:31,410 --> 00:18:32,544
Hi, Eul-wang.

243
00:18:32,711 --> 00:18:33,779
It's a woman?

244
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:37,483
So that's what happened in the end.

245
00:18:39,318 --> 00:18:41,420
Okay. I'll be right there.

246
00:18:43,455 --> 00:18:44,656
Hello, Mr. Park.

247
00:18:45,157 --> 00:18:47,993
I just sent you the press release
by e-mail.

248
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:49,528
Please take a look.

249
00:18:52,431 --> 00:18:54,066
ONE-PERSON PROTEST
AGAINST UNFAIR DISMISSAL

250
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:58,070
It won't be easy, Eul-wang.

251
00:18:58,637 --> 00:19:02,074
Mr. Sim dragged you into this just to hold
a disciplinary meeting against you.

252
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:03,842
You'll be fine.

253
00:19:04,009 --> 00:19:05,878
It's not like you really were involved.

254
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,346
Ms. Lee!

255
00:19:09,882 --> 00:19:12,184
Didn't I tell you to keep a distance
from me at work?

256
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:15,454
I'll stop you guys from getting fired
by all means--

257
00:19:15,521 --> 00:19:17,589
-No.
-We'd rather get fired.

258
00:19:18,357 --> 00:19:19,424
What?

259
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:22,728
Even if get to keep my job this time,
my contract will be over in three months.

