You can give them back to us and leave.

529
00:41:25,416 --> 00:41:27,084
We understand.

530
00:41:46,704 --> 00:41:48,439
The number you have called
cannot be reached...

531
00:41:50,641 --> 00:41:52,710
Why isn't she picking up her phone?

532
00:41:54,478 --> 00:41:55,579
Could she be

533
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:58,349
still there?

534
00:42:01,886 --> 00:42:03,554
Please sign our petition.

535
00:42:03,787 --> 00:42:05,055
Sign our petition.

536
00:42:05,122 --> 00:42:06,423
Please take this.

537
00:42:07,157 --> 00:42:09,593
Excuse me. Please
take a look at this. Thank you.

538
00:42:10,327 --> 00:42:12,997
Excuse me. Please take a look at this.

539
00:42:13,264 --> 00:42:15,065
-Permanent employment!
-Permanent employment!

540
00:42:17,601 --> 00:42:19,169
-Permanent employment!
-Permanent employment!

541
00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:24,742
Mr. Do.

542
00:42:24,808 --> 00:42:25,876
STEP DOWN, EVIL CEO!

543
00:42:30,247 --> 00:42:31,282
Well...

544
00:42:34,485 --> 00:42:35,686
Did you eat?

545
00:42:36,921 --> 00:42:38,923
We're on a hunger strike.

546
00:42:42,459 --> 00:42:43,761
Is that where you're going to sleep?

547
00:42:47,865 --> 00:42:49,166
I'll spend the night here,

548
00:42:49,233 --> 00:42:53,103
but tomorrow, I'll work as usual...

549
00:42:59,877 --> 00:43:02,079
I'm sorry, Mr. Do.

550
00:43:28,205 --> 00:43:29,306
It's cold.

551
00:43:52,596 --> 00:43:53,964
You're early.

552
00:43:55,099 --> 00:43:57,401
Can you come in for a moment?

553
00:44:12,850 --> 00:44:13,917
Ta-da.

554
00:44:18,088 --> 00:44:19,223
Pig's trotters?

555
00:44:19,390 --> 00:44:20,524
Come here.

556
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:30,868
While no one is watching,

557
00:44:30,934 --> 00:44:33,837
eat some food
before you go out and protest.

558
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:37,741
I can't.

559
00:44:37,908 --> 00:44:39,677
Don't be like that.

560
00:44:39,743 --> 00:44:41,612
Have just one piece.

561
00:44:47,651 --> 00:44:50,020
This is the second day
of the hunger strike. This is not okay.

562
00:44:50,821 --> 00:44:51,989
The secretaries are

563
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:54,425
doing this

564
00:44:54,491 --> 00:44:56,427
because there's nothing else they can do.

565
00:45:01,331 --> 00:45:02,466
Don't go there.

566
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:03,901
Mr. Do.

567
00:45:04,668 --> 00:45:07,104
I don't care if you shout

568
00:45:07,171 --> 00:45:10,107
I should step down or die out there.

569
00:45:10,507 --> 00:45:13,977
But I don't want you to stand there
all day without eating anything

570
00:45:14,111 --> 00:45:16,280
or sleep under a cardboard box
in the cold.

571
00:45:16,513 --> 00:45:19,249
I also don't want people on the street
to feel sorry for you

572
00:45:19,316 --> 00:45:20,751
and whisper about you.

573
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:23,821
So

574
00:45:24,922 --> 00:45:26,390
have just one piece.

575
00:45:31,795 --> 00:45:32,863
Even when I'm

576
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:37,468
out protesting,

577
00:45:38,502 --> 00:45:40,137
I can't stop feeling sorry for you

578
00:45:40,204 --> 00:45:42,339
and thinking about you.
It's driving me crazy.

579
00:45:44,141 --> 00:45:47,745
I want you to eat well.

580
00:45:48,212 --> 00:45:49,546
You don't have to worry about me.

581
00:45:51,749 --> 00:45:54,184
I promise I'll come back

582
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:57,454
strong and healthy after the protest.

583
00:46:04,161 --> 00:46:05,496
HUNGER STRIKE, DAY 3

584
00:46:08,832 --> 00:46:10,768
What do we do now?

585
00:46:11,468 --> 00:46:14,772
None of the reporters who interviewed us
are writing any articles.

586
00:46:15,205 --> 00:46:17,941
Mr. Sim won't bat an eye.

587
00:46:18,642 --> 00:46:19,977
Guys, tear everything down!

588
00:46:20,043 --> 00:46:21,011
-Yes!
-Yes!

589
00:46:21,078 --> 00:46:23,347
If you're tired, go home and sleep!

590
00:46:23,480 --> 00:46:25,649
-Why are you sleeping here?
-Get out of here!

591
00:46:25,716 --> 00:46:28,152
-What are you doing? Stop!
-Get out!

592
00:46:28,952 --> 00:46:30,020
No!

593
00:46:30,087 --> 00:46:31,421
-Do as I say!
-Hurry up!

594
00:46:31,488 --> 00:46:33,590
This isn't going to change anything.

595
00:46:33,657 --> 00:46:35,526
-Let go.
-I feel sorry for you.

596
00:46:35,592 --> 00:46:37,094
-I said let go!
-There's no point...

597
00:46:38,228 --> 00:46:39,630
Who are you?

598
00:46:39,696 --> 00:46:40,864
Mr. Do.

599
00:46:43,567 --> 00:46:46,336
Well, I appreciate your hard work.

600
00:46:47,004 --> 00:46:48,305
Who am I?

601
00:46:54,545 --> 00:46:58,315
"Director of T&T Mobile Media Team One"?

602
00:46:59,583 --> 00:47:00,684
That's right.

603
00:47:02,886 --> 00:47:03,954
Do you see this?

604
00:47:05,088 --> 00:47:06,623
"The beginning of power abuse,

605
00:47:06,690 --> 00:47:09,660
Chairman Do Wan-bae." That's my father.

606
00:47:09,726 --> 00:47:10,961
"The corrupt and bribed CEO,

607
00:47:11,028 --> 00:47:12,763
Sim Hae-yong." That's my uncle.

608
00:47:14,698 --> 00:47:15,833
And then

609
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:19,770
"No to the second generation."
This jerk happens to be

610
00:47:20,537 --> 00:47:21,839
me.

611
00:47:22,706 --> 00:47:26,343
May I ask why you're here?

612
00:47:26,877 --> 00:47:30,314
I can take care of this. You may go back.

613
00:47:30,380 --> 00:47:34,017
But this was Mr. Sim's order.

614
00:47:36,453 --> 00:47:39,456
I'll talk to Uncle later.

615
00:47:39,890 --> 00:47:42,459
Don't worry and go back.

616
00:47:42,526 --> 00:47:44,194
It's not that I'm worried.

617
00:47:44,261 --> 00:47:46,430
-You can go back.
-It's just...

618
00:47:46,496 --> 00:47:47,931
-Go back now.
-Okay.

619
00:47:47,998 --> 00:47:49,900
-Be polite.
-We'll be going.

620
00:47:49,967 --> 00:47:51,168
Please talk to Mr. Sim.

621
00:47:51,235 --> 00:47:53,470
We trust you.

622
00:47:53,570 --> 00:47:54,671
Let's go.

623
00:48:07,217 --> 00:48:10,954
Your CT scan results haven't changed much.

624
00:48:11,588 --> 00:48:13,924
Enough of that.

625
00:48:13,991 --> 00:48:16,126
Please take a careful look
at the ingredients.

626
00:48:16,393 --> 00:48:18,629
It's over-the-counter cold medicine.

627
00:48:18,695 --> 00:48:20,564
Can it be taken on an empty stomach?

628
00:48:21,965 --> 00:48:23,901
When did she last eat?

629
00:48:24,201 --> 00:48:26,270
About three days ago.

630
00:48:26,703 --> 00:48:27,804
What?

631
00:48:28,038 --> 00:48:30,407
Then what she needs is food, not medicine.

632
00:48:30,474 --> 00:48:32,409
She won't eat. That's why I'm doing this.

633
00:48:32,476 --> 00:48:34,077
Go and make her eat something first.

634
00:48:34,478 --> 00:48:37,114
Or bring her to the emergency room
so we can give her some fluids.

635
00:48:40,717 --> 00:48:42,386
She won't come to the hospital either.

636
00:48:43,587 --> 00:48:46,056
By the way,

637
00:48:46,623 --> 00:48:50,294
have you seen any other faces
since the funeral?

638
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:54,665
I've told you about
Dr. Park's patient in the US, right?

639
00:48:54,798 --> 00:48:55,966
Recently--

640
00:48:56,033 --> 00:48:58,201
There's a starving and sick
person out there.

641
00:48:58,268 --> 00:48:59,336
Who cares about faces?

642
00:48:59,403 --> 00:49:00,537
Goodness.

643
00:49:00,804 --> 00:49:02,272
You were willing to give me anything

644
00:49:02,339 --> 00:49:04,274
as long as I made you see faces.

645
00:49:04,675 --> 00:49:07,010
Who says medicine has come a long way?

646
00:49:07,644 --> 00:49:10,080
There isn't even medicine
that can be taken on an empty stomach yet.

647
00:49:12,582 --> 00:49:13,850
Give me that.

648
00:49:18,522 --> 00:49:21,558
Why did I ever operate
on that crazy idiot?

649
00:49:22,659 --> 00:49:26,163
Aren't you going to do anything
about the secretaries and drivers?

650
00:49:26,997 --> 00:49:28,799
They haven't eaten for three days.

651
00:49:29,099 --> 00:49:30,400
I know.

652
00:49:30,500 --> 00:49:32,402
They've been such a nuisance.

653
00:49:32,536 --> 00:49:35,005
That's why I was going to clean
everything up. Why did you stop it?

654
00:49:35,205 --> 00:49:37,140
If you hadn't violated
the dispatched labor law

655
00:49:37,341 --> 00:49:38,775
and compensated the employees properly,

656
00:49:38,842 --> 00:49:40,644
they wouldn't be doing this now.

657
00:49:41,044 --> 00:49:42,512
Have you lost your mind?

658
00:49:42,579 --> 00:49:44,748
They're the ones
who pocketed company funds.

659
00:49:45,382 --> 00:49:46,683
And you're accusing me?

660
00:49:48,285 --> 00:49:50,020
If you can't hire them directly
immediately,

661
00:49:50,253 --> 00:49:53,123
at least start a negotiation
so that they can stop their hunger strike.

662
00:49:53,523 --> 00:49:55,859
If I was going to negotiate with them,
I wouldn't have started.

663
00:49:56,360 --> 00:49:58,495
I should step up and get rid of them

664
00:49:58,895 --> 00:50:00,831
to win the directors over to my side.

665
00:50:00,897 --> 00:50:04,001
Are you saying you're ignoring them
to keep your CEO position?

666
00:50:04,067 --> 00:50:05,502
What else can I do?

667
00:50:05,936 --> 00:50:07,437
Even after revealing that you're ill,

668
00:50:08,105 --> 00:50:10,140
I'm barely holding onto my position.

669
00:50:21,918 --> 00:50:23,153
Hello, Ms. Park.

670
00:50:24,121 --> 00:50:25,489
You're here.

671
00:50:25,555 --> 00:50:28,125
Why did you want to see me here?

672
00:50:29,526 --> 00:50:31,294
Do you see this building?

673
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:37,267
It's Gwangbak Building.
It belongs to your daughter, right?

674
00:50:37,401 --> 00:50:40,737
You sure are one ambitious man,
aren't you?

675
00:50:41,271 --> 00:50:44,474
You already seem to take
such a keen interest in our property.

676
00:50:44,775 --> 00:50:46,176
Why are we here?

677
00:50:46,243 --> 00:50:47,477
Listen, you punk.

678
00:50:49,546 --> 00:50:53,984
I would've loved
to take you to the cleaners,

679
00:50:55,919 --> 00:50:58,388
but that'd apparently make me broke too,

680
00:50:59,289 --> 00:51:01,124
so I decided to offer you this building.

681
00:51:01,491 --> 00:51:03,960
Take this and leave my daughter alone.

682
00:51:04,094 --> 00:51:06,563
One building can't break us up.

683
00:51:08,498 --> 00:51:10,000
But I can't give you two!

684
00:51:10,467 --> 00:51:12,169
There's something
I haven't told you about me.

685
00:51:13,236 --> 00:51:15,505
I only buy things I'll keep
for more than 10 years

686
00:51:16,006 --> 00:51:18,175
and date women I'm willing to spend
the rest of my life with.

687
00:51:18,341 --> 00:51:22,179
You're nothing but a toy
I got for my daughter!

688
00:51:22,245 --> 00:51:24,014
That sounds

689
00:51:24,815 --> 00:51:26,249
pretty amazing to me.

690
00:51:27,617 --> 00:51:31,154
That means I can make her smile
and make her happy.

691
00:51:32,255 --> 00:51:34,624
I'd love to be your daughter's toy
for the rest of my life.

692
00:51:55,612 --> 00:51:57,180
I hear the secretaries are
causing trouble.

693
00:52:05,422 --> 00:52:06,490
What's this?

694
00:52:06,556 --> 00:52:08,725
You sounded so confident,
so I thought, "Why not?"

695
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:11,027
Eat this and become the new CEO.

696
00:52:20,303 --> 00:52:21,638
Why are you just standing there?

697
00:52:29,646 --> 00:52:33,016
I'm sorry. I don't think I can eat this.

698
00:52:33,450 --> 00:52:35,852
Haven't you been pestering me for it
all this time?

699
00:52:36,253 --> 00:52:37,454
I know.

700
00:52:39,456 --> 00:52:40,690
This is

701
00:52:41,858 --> 00:52:44,094
the first samgyetang
you've made for me in 20 years.

702
00:52:45,529 --> 00:52:47,063
I would've loved to eat it.

703
00:52:51,001 --> 00:52:52,068
I'm sorry.

704
00:52:53,603 --> 00:52:54,838
I'm really sorry, Mom.

705
00:53:10,754 --> 00:53:12,856
MEDICINE

706
00:53:23,967 --> 00:53:26,203
I should step up and get rid of them

707
00:53:26,536 --> 00:53:28,605
to win the directors over to my side.

708
00:53:36,713 --> 00:53:40,050
Hi, it's me. Where are you?

709
00:53:47,891 --> 00:53:50,727
What's going on?
Why did you bring me here?

710
00:53:51,962 --> 00:53:55,432
It took me a while before I could call you
after hearing about your mother.

711
00:53:56,533 --> 00:53:59,102
I've had too much on my mind.

712
00:53:59,469 --> 00:54:02,439
I haven't been able to call you
for the same reason. I'm sorry.

713
00:54:03,540 --> 00:54:05,208
It was for me

714
00:54:05,408 --> 00:54:07,978
that Ms. Lee started all this.

715
00:54:09,045 --> 00:54:10,213
And as a result,

716
00:54:10,981 --> 00:54:12,582
you got hurt.

717
00:54:12,649 --> 00:54:13,783
Are you crazy?

718
00:54:14,517 --> 00:54:17,053
After hearing how your mother passed away,

719
00:54:17,787 --> 00:54:19,356
how could you support me at the meeting?

720
00:54:19,422 --> 00:54:23,360
I feel enough resentment
for your father though, so don't worry.

721
00:54:26,963 --> 00:54:28,832
Who is the suit for?

722
00:54:31,067 --> 00:54:32,202
Me?

723
00:54:32,869 --> 00:54:34,070
I'd like to get my wifey

724
00:54:35,472 --> 00:54:36,806
a suit.

725
00:54:37,107 --> 00:54:38,608
Just a moment, please.

726
00:54:41,077 --> 00:54:42,412
You're the crazy one.

727
00:54:42,512 --> 00:54:44,381
Why would you get a suit
for an unemployed man?

728
00:54:44,681 --> 00:54:47,150
You'll need it soon.

729
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:51,788
Dae-ju.

730
00:54:52,722 --> 00:54:54,658
I'm trying to make a plan,

731
00:54:55,191 --> 00:54:57,160
and I need your help.

732
00:55:00,563 --> 00:55:02,565
T&T MOBILE CEO APPLICATION LETTER

733
00:55:06,569 --> 00:55:07,537
What's this?

734
00:55:07,604 --> 00:55:09,272
I got it back
from the administrative office.

735
00:55:15,545 --> 00:55:16,646
What are you doing?

736
00:55:16,713 --> 00:55:19,382
I withdraw my application
for the CEO position.

737
00:55:19,783 --> 00:55:20,884
What?

738
00:55:21,251 --> 00:55:23,920
It means I give up.

739
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:28,425
If you drop out,
I'm the only candidate left.

740
00:55:29,292 --> 00:55:30,660
Do you expect me to believe you?

741
00:55:31,027 --> 00:55:32,462
There's one condition.

742
00:55:35,432 --> 00:55:37,300
I want to go home.

743
00:55:40,170 --> 00:55:42,405
I miss my mom.

744
00:55:44,974 --> 00:55:46,876
I want to take a shower.

745
00:55:49,145 --> 00:55:50,647
I want to eat chicken.

746
00:56:08,565 --> 00:56:10,867
HUNGER STRIKE, DAY 4

747
00:56:15,672 --> 00:56:16,806
Ms. Jeong.

748
00:56:18,641 --> 00:56:20,543
You didn't have to come out here.

749
00:56:22,579 --> 00:56:26,316
What's the food you're craving
the most right now?

750
00:56:27,784 --> 00:56:28,985
Why are you asking that?

751
00:56:29,052 --> 00:56:30,954
Pig's trotters? Pizza?

752
00:56:32,956 --> 00:56:34,858
I could eat anything right now.

753
00:56:34,924 --> 00:56:36,192
What about chicken or hamburgers?

754
00:56:36,860 --> 00:56:38,094
That sounds awesome.

755
00:56:39,829 --> 00:56:42,198
No. I can't eat, Mr. Do.

756
00:56:45,835 --> 00:56:46,936
Right.

757
00:56:47,103 --> 00:56:48,805
I'm sure you're craving a lot of things,

758
00:56:50,106 --> 00:56:53,243
but after starving for four days,
it's probably best to start with porridge.

759
00:56:58,014 --> 00:56:58,948
Get up.

760
00:57:00,817 --> 00:57:03,686
Take this off and
come have porridge with me.

761
00:57:07,323 --> 00:57:09,626
Mr. Do, please don't do this.

762
00:57:10,393 --> 00:57:12,629
Everyone, go back now.

763
00:57:13,430 --> 00:57:16,433
The company is ready
to start a negotiation with you.

764
00:57:16,933 --> 00:57:19,135
You can go back and eat now.

765
00:57:20,403 --> 00:57:22,172
What are you talking about?

766
00:57:22,505 --> 00:57:24,774
I've talked to Mr. Sim.

767
00:57:24,841 --> 00:57:26,209
There will be an announcement tomorrow.

768
00:57:26,276 --> 00:57:28,611
He said he'd give you more details
over the phone.

769
00:57:30,046 --> 00:57:31,114
CEO SIM HAE-YONG

770
00:57:32,415 --> 00:57:33,583
Take it, Ms. Lee.

771
00:57:35,885 --> 00:57:38,521
Lee Eul-wang speaking. Pardon?

772
00:57:39,689 --> 00:57:43,326
Okay. Tomorrow at 2 p.m. I see.

773
00:57:56,105 --> 00:57:57,674
We did it!

774
00:58:01,778 --> 00:58:02,879
Are you so happy?

775
00:58:03,012 --> 00:58:06,049
Yes, I am. I couldn't be happier.

776
00:58:06,783 --> 00:58:09,853
The secretaries don't have to worry
about getting fired anymore.

777
00:58:10,086 --> 00:58:13,323
I can also eat anything I want now.

778
00:58:13,823 --> 00:58:16,092
But more than anything,

779
00:58:16,159 --> 00:58:20,296
I'll be the CEO's secretary
in just a few days.

780
00:58:27,770 --> 00:58:29,239
Why are you looking at me like that?

781
00:58:29,305 --> 00:58:30,373
What?

782
00:58:32,342 --> 00:58:34,811
I'm happy that you're happy.

783
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:41,017
I really wish I could show you
how my face looks right now.

784
00:58:41,284 --> 00:58:43,720
I want you to see how happy I look.

785
00:58:43,853 --> 00:58:44,954
Then

786
00:58:46,422 --> 00:58:48,157
show me how happy you are

787
00:58:50,493 --> 00:58:52,929
by holding me tight.

788
00:59:28,965 --> 00:59:30,967
Subtitle translation by Min-jin Kim

